---
title: Clawless フック処理フロー（Hook Processing Sequence）
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User (VS Code)
    participant CC as Claude Code Agent
    participant Pre as PreToolUse Hooks
    participant Tool as Tool Execution
    participant Post as PostToolUse Hooks
    participant Evidence as evidence-ledger.jsonl

    User->>CC: Prompt / Task instruction

    Note over CC: Claude Code selects tool<br/>(Bash, Edit, Write, Read, MCP...)

    CC->>Pre: Tool call request
    activate Pre

    Note over Pre: 1. clawless-permission.sh<br/>   → 4-category classify<br/>   (Read-only/Agent/Exec/Write)
    Note over Pre: 2. clawless-injection-guard.sh<br/>   → 50+ pattern scan<br/>   → NFKC normalization
    Note over Pre: 3. clawless-evasion-guard.sh<br/>   → 7 evasion vector check<br/>   → Path canonicalization
    Note over Pre: 4. clawless-quiet-inject.sh<br/>   → Token optimization flags
    Note over Pre: 5. clawless-data-boundary.sh<br/>   → Jurisdiction verification

    alt Any hook returns "block"
        Pre-->>CC: ❌ { "decision": "block", "reason": "..." }
        CC-->>User: Tool blocked — reason displayed
    else All hooks pass
        Pre->>Tool: ✅ { "decision": "allow" } or "modify" with additionalContext
        deactivate Pre
        activate Tool

        Tool->>Post: Execution result
        deactivate Tool
        activate Post

        Note over Post: 1. clawless-evidence.sh<br/>   → SHA-256 hash chain append
        Note over Post: 2. clawless-exfil-guard.sh<br/>   → Data leak pattern check
        Note over Post: 3. clawless-dep-audit.sh<br/>   → Dependency security scan<br/>   (if npm/pip install detected)

        Post->>Evidence: Append JSONL entry with hash

        alt Exfil pattern detected
            Post-->>CC: ⚠️ Warning + additionalContext
        end

        Post->>CC: Result passed through
        deactivate Post
        CC->>User: Tool output displayed
    end
